Seems so simple, doesn’t it? Truth is, there are 3 dimensions of time. Past, Present, and Future. 

Sadly, most of us destroy much of our present lives regretting the past OR worrying and catastrophizing about the future. 

It makes it very VERY hard to live peacefully in the present when we do that. 

So, don’t do that. “Protect your peace” as it’s said. 

If we don’t, someday, in the future, we will learn that every present we ever had has become a regrettable past. 

Break the cycle. Let the past go. Live for the present every moment and enjoy it. It happens only once in a lifetime. 

❤️❤️❤️to all. 

#mentalhealth #liftwithcorbinallred #depression #livepresently #bepresentlypeaceful #anxiety #letthepastgo

The U.S.A. 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸 

It’s not perfect, but there are a whole lot of wonderful people here who call this place home…including those I love the most. 

I’m grateful to live here…I’m grateful to be an American. 

I am grateful for the freedoms I cherish…that did not come without the profound sacrifices of those who took significant risks before me. 

I am grateful for all of those who have done dangerous things in my behalf. 

It will never be lost on me that many people have and continue to fight and die to provide me this life.

I believe, with all my heart, in the foundational goodness and fundamental potential of this country…not because we’re without flaw, but because we can individually and collectively recognize flaw…and live in a place where “WE THE PEOPLE” have the power and capacity to change it.

Happy 4th of July to EVERY SINGLE AMERICAN. 🇺🇸🇺🇸🇺🇸

WARNING: Viewer discretion advised. Themes include suicide awareness, anti-bullying, depression, among others. 

If you’re having thoughts of suicide, STOP. Tell someone you know and trust and CALL 1-800-273-8255 NOW. There IS help. 

Here is the full film.

After witnessing the overwhelming response to the film, and after literally thousands of requests, we’ve decided to make my short film, ALL THAT MATTERS, available to view in its entirety on Instagram.

With all that can be found on social media these days, I felt that this might be one of the most important things out there right now…at least to somebody…and that’s enough reason for me to share it wherever I can. 

My hope in making this film was that it might actually change the way we look at our lives…or better still…that it might actually change the way we live our lives.

Please watch, share, and follow.

If you like the film, please comment and tag family members or friends you think might benefit from seeing it. 

If you have teenage children and feel it appropriate for their age, PLEASE show them. 

Have the conversations. Ask the questions. Open the door. 

Talk about suicide with those you love! Talk bullying. Talk about things we can do to help those who are struggling. 

The message isn’t new, it’s just been forgotten by too many of us. 

I needed the reminder myself. Now, I’ll never forget. I hope it’s the same for you.

Thank you in advance for your support. And remember, my next film, STICKS AND STONES, launches this month on YouTube. 

Be kind to each other.

WATCH TO THE END

latestIgtvVideos.title: Who or what is keeping you from falling?
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
PLEASE SHARE! 

Life is hard! The climbing is tough. Sometimes, on purpose or by accident, we find ourselves in precarious situations in life where we are at great risk of falling and hurting ourselves. Sometimes, we try to do it alone, ropeless, free climbing the cliff face of life. Oftentimes, when we do it alone, it has disastrous consequences. I would NEVER recommend this approach. I’ve seen the ramifications too many times. 

Sometimes, unfortunately and all too often, we think that tying into intangible pacifiers like social media will keep us safe. We think it will keep us from falling. We turn to it for council. guidance, love, affection, praise, and support. Well, I’m here to tell you, social media is NOT paying attention and COULD NOT care less about dropping you. Social media is not capable of providing you with ANYTHING you really need. It’s NOT REAL!!! Social media is NOT a good climbing partner. It’ll make you think you’re safe, it’ll even make you feel confident in taking the absolutely wrong route. It’ll make you feel weak a moment after telling you you’re strong. It’ll cheer you on when it thinks you’re doing well and mock you unmercifully when you’re struggling. It’ll drop you over and over and over again and then make you feel guilty for not trusting it. So you’ll tie in again.

TIME TO FIND A NEW CLIMBING PARTNER!!! 

When it comes to life, we need to tie into our ropes with real people on the other end of it...people who are present, tangible, trustworthy, loyal...people who actually love us...people who care deeply for our success and are paying attention and are fully committed to our climb and to never EVER letting us fall. 

God will ALWAYS hold the rope. Loving family members will ALWAYS hold the rope. Good, close, present, dependable friends will ALWAYS hold the rope. 

Why? Because, unlike social media and smart phones, they CARE ABOUT YOU!!! 

Is social media all bad? No. But it can’t be your life line! 

When you’re tying into the climb of life, make sure you know who or what is holding on to the other end of your rope. 

#findlovelift
